				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There are only 4 posts that i see so far to the downtime issues that Brad has brought up again.  These commensts seem to be quick and abrasive, seemingly to me from less experianced players.  In the respect i use &quot;experiance&quot; i don't mean what level there character is i mean just what exactly they have done.  I travel with a group of my Real life friends in EQ.  This was very convient for us being we all live in seperate parts of the state now due to going to college.  What we have over almost any group is a working knowledge of how to work to gether.  With our working together our group has done feats that amaze all who look upon us.  for example our group of characters playing on test and actually rather underequiped to be in Solesek were abel to kill a clockwork gnome while our average char level was 21.  The gnome was 6-9 levels above us.  We all gained the FULL amount of exp achievable from a single kill (we believe that to be about one fith of a bub).  <BR>
<BR>
As a group we travel the land and hunt what we dare (quite alot for who we are).  In this people die.  We loese time that we have commited but what we have really gained for $10 a month is an &quot;activity&quot; where we can all get together.  In my thinking there really isn't down time but more time to talk to your friends.  Be this in traveling across the lands, waiting for the group to ready for battle, or as a castor looking at your book.  Always on your screen you can talk to, hear from, and take in an experiance shared by others.  <BR>
<BR>
What many people don't realize as they wine about this and that is to really have something, anything, about a game make it so bad as people think down time is then why would they play it.  As a general rule players of EQ should open their eyes, look at their played time on their primary characters and figure out if for $10 a month they could have filled all of that time half as enjoyably as they did playing eq.  if they can more power to them and leave some of that pricy band with for the rest of us (or maybe some server space;)<BR>
<BR>
my 2 cp<BR>
Gantores
